⸻



1) OVERVIEW



HexQuest is a 2-player strategic fantasy game that blends territory control, deterministic tactical combat, and card-driven progression.



Players compete to expand territory, build infrastructure, deploy units, and defeat each other’s Capital to win.

Games last up to 30 turns and end with either:

	•	Capital destruction (instant win),

	•	80% territory control (instant win), or

	•	Highest Victory Points at Turn 30.



⸻



2) COMPONENTS & DEFINITIONS



Entities

	•	Hexes: the board spaces

	•	Units: persistent combatants

	•	Buildings: infrastructure

	•	Capital: special building with HP + defense

	•	Cards: creatures, buildings, tech, tactical

	•	Players: P1 and P2



⸻



3) MAP & TERRAIN



Board

	•	127 hexes total



Terrain Types & Combat defense

Terrain

Defense

Movement

Plains

+0

1 action

