Strategic Objective Hexes

	•	3 designated at setup

	•	Only relevant for scoring



⸻



4) FOG OF WAR & VISION



Vision is asymmetric:



Owner territory

	•	Full visibility of terrain, units, buildings



Enemy territory

	•	Visible only within 3 hexes of any hex you control

	•	Outside this radius: unknown/gray



Unclaimed

	•	Unknown unless in vision radius



UI may fade color by distance — purely visual.



⸻



5) SETUP



Each player:

	•	Places Capital on opposite edges

	•	Starts with 1 Tier-1 unit on Capital

	•	Energy: P1=5, P2=6 (balance)

	•	Knowledge: 3

	•	Deck: 30 cards

	•	Hand: 5 cards



Mirrored halves for terrain generation.



⸻



6) TURN STRUCTURE



Start Phase

	1.	UPKEEP (before income):

	•	Command limit check + upkeep

	2.	INCOME:

	•	+1 Energy per controlled hex

	•	Capital: +1 Energy, +1 Knowledge

	•	Knowledge structures

	3.	DRAW:

	•	Draw 2 keep 1

	4.	ACTIONS:

	•	Reset to 4 (max 6 with tech)

	5.	UPDATE:

	•	Tier unlocks based on hex count



Action Phase

	•	Spend actions on:

MOVE, ATTACK, PLAY_CARD, PLAY_TECH, PLAY_TACTICAL, ACTIVATE_BUILDING, END_TURN



End Phase

	•	Healing

	•	Discard down to hand limit

	•	Check win conditions



⸻



7) MOVEMENT, ZOC & STACKING



Movement

	•	1 action per hex (mountain = 2)

	•	Max 3 units per hex

	•	Can split stacks before moving



Zone of Control

	•	Entering adjacency to an enemy stops movement

	•	Units may move away freely at turn start



Attack interaction

	•	Units that attack cannot move again that turn



⸻



8) COMBAT (DETERMINISTIC)



All combat calculates damage without randomness.



Defense Value = terrain + adjacency + buildings

	•	terrainDEF: Plains 0, Forest 100, Mountain 175, River 0, Capital 250

	•	adjacencyDEF: +75 per adjacent friendly hex (max 225; 300 with tech)

	•	buildingDEF: Fortification +150 (+50 if fortified with tech)



Damage = max(0, attackerATK - DefenseValue)

	•	Defender does not strike back

	•	Damage persists

	•	If HP <= 0: defender destroyed, hex may be captured



River Rule

If defender hex=River and attacker not on River:

	•	attacker ATK -100



Adjacency Soft Decay

If a unit takes >0 damage this turn:

	•	adjacency bonus in that hex is reduced by 75 until end of attacker’s turn

	•	resets at start of defender’s turn



⸻



9) CAPITAL SIEGE



Capital:

	•	HP: 1600

	•	DEF: +250

	•	Cannot host other buildings



To attack:

	•	attacker must control 2 adjacent hexes to Capital



Destroying Capital = instant win.



⸻



10) ECONOMY & COMMAND LIMIT



Resources

	•	Energy for units/buildings

	•	Knowledge for tech



Income

	•	+1 Energy per hex

	•	Capital: +1 Energy, +1 Knowledge



Command Limit

	•	floor(controlledHexes/2)

	•	Upkeep: 2 Energy per excess unit



⸻



11) CARDS & DECK RULES

	•	30-card deck

	•	Draw 2 keep 1

	•	Hand limit = 7 base (expandable with tech)

	•	Deck exhaustion: reshuffle discard into deck



Card types

	•	Creature

	•	Building

	•	Tech (no duplicates)

	•	Tactical (max 2 per combat)



⸻



12) TECH SYSTEM

	•	Tech costs Knowledge + 1 action

	•	Permanent effect, removed from deck when played

	•	Tier-gated by controlled hex count



Examples:

	•	Elite Training: +150 ATK (Tier2+)

	•	Siege Doctrine: ignore building DEF

	•	Advanced Formations: adjacency cap 300

	•	Reinforced Structures: +50 building DEF



⸻



13) SCORING (TURN 30)



If no instant win by end of Turn 30:

	•	1 VP per controlled hex

	•	2 VP per building

	•	Tier1 unit = 1 VP, Tier2 = 3, Tier3 = 5

	•	3 VP per Strategic Objective hex

	•	+5 VP if Capital survives



⸻



14) BUILDINGS



Max 1 building per hex (Capital hex cannot host additional buildings)



Types:

	•	Fortification: +150 DEF

	•	Energy Structure: +2 Energy/turn

	•	Knowledge Structure: +2 Knowledge/turn (+2 if on Ruins)

	•	Healing Structure: +2 HP heal per turn



⸻



15) HEALING



End of each player turn:

	•	Units not attacked this turn heal +1 HP

	•	If on Healing Structure: extra +2 HP



⸻



16) TACTICAL CARDS



Playable only during your own attacks.

Max 2 can affect one combat.



Examples:

	•	+200 ATK

	•	-150 building DEF

	•	+150 DEF

	•	Heal 300 HP



⸻



17) TIER UNLOCKS



Based on controlled hex count:

	•	Tier 1: 1–7

	•	Tier 2: 8–15

	•	Tier 3: 16+



Tier gating applies to creature and tech availability.



⸻



18) EDGE-CASE RULINGS (FINAL)

	•	Attacker chooses target unit in defended hex.

	•	If enemy building exists without units, entering destroys building and captures hex.

	•	Summoned unit can’t attack until owned turn passes.

	•	Command limit upkeep must be paid at start of turn before income.

	•	Tactical cards for prototype are not reactive; only active player plays them.



⸻



19) PROTOTYPING CONVENTIONS

	•	Map is mirrored halves.

	•	Fog based on controlled/vision rules.

	•	River implemented as hex terrain penalty.

	•	Capital hex excluded from additional buildings.


HEXQUEST PROTOTYPE SPEC v1.3 (with Vision v1.0)

CORE
- 2 players. Alternating full turns. Max 30 turns.
- Instant win if: (a) enemy Capital destroyed OR (b) a player controls >=80% of all hexes.
- If no instant win by end of Turn 30: score VP (see SCORING).

MAP
- Board: 127 hexes (hex grid). Terrain types: PLAINS, FOREST, MOUNTAIN, RIVER, RUINS.
- Terrain combat defense: PLAINS +0, FOREST +100, MOUNTAIN +175, RIVER +0, RUINS +0, CAPITAL +250 (capital hex only).
- River combat rule (simple): if defender hex terrain=RIVER and attacker’s current hex terrain!=RIVER, attacker ATK -100 (before damage).
- 3 Strategic Objective hexes are designated at setup (VP only; no active effects).

FOG / VISION
- Each player always fully sees: all hexes they control (terrain, units, buildings).
- Each player sees enemy territory only within VISION RADIUS = 3 hexes from ANY hex they control.
- Outside vision: render as unknown gray (no terrain/units/buildings shown).
- Unclaimed hexes are unknown gray unless within vision radius (then terrain can be shown if you choose; prototype may keep them gray until claimed—UI choice).
- “Distance fade” is UI-only: apply fading based on distance 0–3; no gameplay effect.

SETUP
- Each player places a Capital on opposite edges of the map.
- Starting resources: P1 Energy=5, Knowledge=3; P2 Energy=6, Knowledge=3 (Player 2 compensation).
- Each player starts with 1 Tier-1 unit on their Capital.
- Deck: 30 cards. Starting hand: 5 (draw 2 keep 1 repeatedly until 5, or draw 5 directly—prototype may simplify to draw 5).

TURN STRUCTURE
Start Phase (in order):
1) UPKEEP (before income): if unitsOwned > commandLimit, pay 2 Energy per excess unit. If cannot pay, destroy excess units (owner chooses) until affordable.
2) INCOME: +1 Energy per controlled hex.
3) CAPITAL INCOME: +1 Energy and +1 Knowledge.
4) STRUCTURE INCOME: Knowledge structures generate knowledge (see BUILDINGS).
5) DRAW: draw 2 cards, keep 1, discard the other (to discard pile).
6) ACTIONS: set actions to 4 base (plus tech), hard cap 6.
7) TIER UPDATE: recalc tier based on controlled hexes; tier applies immediately.

Action Phase:
- Spend actions on: MOVE, ATTACK, PLAY_CREATURE, PLAY_BUILDING, PLAY_TECH, PLAY_TACTICAL, ACTIVATE_BUILDING, END_TURN.
- Each unit may ATTACK at most once per its owner’s turn.
- If a unit ATTACKS, it cannot MOVE again that turn.
- Summoned units (played this turn) cannot ATTACK until next turn (“summoning sickness”).

End Phase:
- HEALING: units not attacked this turn heal +1 HP (up to maxHP). If on a Healing Structure, heal +2 additional.
- HAND LIMIT: discard down to hand limit 7 (base; upgrades later).
- Check win conditions.

MOVEMENT / STACKING / ZOC
- Max 3 units per hex.
- MOVE (stack): 1 action to move selected units from a hex to an adjacent hex (subject to cap).
- MOUNTAIN movement cost: moving into a MOUNTAIN hex costs 2 actions (unless a tech changes it).
- ZOC: when a moving unit enters a hex adjacent to any enemy unit, its movement ends immediately. (Still allowed to attack later if it hasn’t attacked yet.)
- Disengage: if a unit starts adjacent to enemy, it may move away normally (no penalty).

CONTROL / CAPTURE / BUILDINGS ON CAPTURE
- A hex is controlled by a player if it contains that player’s units and no enemy units.
- If a player enters an enemy-controlled hex that contains no enemy units but has an enemy building: capture the hex and DESTROY that building (prototype rule).
- Capital hex cannot host other buildings.

COMBAT (DETERMINISTIC, NO RETALIATION)
- ATTACK: costs 1 action; attacker must be adjacent to target hex.
- Target selection: attacker chooses which defending unit in target hex takes damage.
- DefenseValue = terrainDEF + adjacencyDEF + buildingDEF (+ capitalDEF if capital hex).
  - adjacencyDEF = 75 * (# adjacent friendly hexes to target that have >=1 defender’s unit), cap 225; cap 300 if tech “Advanced Formations” is active for defender.
  - buildingDEF: Fortification +150; if defender has “Reinforced Structures”, buildingDEF +50 (i.e., Fort becomes 200).
- Damage = max(0, attackerATK - DefenseValue). Apply to defender HP. Defender does not strike back.
- If damage > 0, apply ADJACENCY SOFT DECAY to that target hex for remainder of attacker’s turn: reduce its adjacency contribution by 75 (min 0), once per hex per turn; resets at start of defender’s next turn.
- If defender HP <= 0: destroy unit immediately. If no enemy units remain on hex, attacker captures the hex.

CAPITAL SIEGE
- Capital stats: HP 1600, DEF +250. No retaliation. No extra buildings on capital hex.
- To ATTACK a Capital, attacker must control at least 2 hexes adjacent to the Capital at the moment of attack.
- Destroying enemy Capital = instant win.

ECONOMY / COMMAND LIMIT
- Energy & Knowledge accumulate indefinitely.
- Income: +1 Energy per controlled hex. Capital adds +1 Energy +1 Knowledge each start phase.
- CommandLimit = floor(controlledHexes / 2).
- Upkeep: 2 Energy per unit above limit (paid before income).

TIERS / GATING
- Tier by controlled hexes: Tier1=1–7, Tier2=8–15, Tier3=16+.
- Tier gates: stronger creature cards and higher-tier tech cards.
- Tech duplicates: not allowed (unless explicitly stated).

CARDS
- Draw: draw 2 keep 1 each turn (discard other).
- Hand limit: 7 base.
- Deck empty: reshuffle discard into deck.
- Tactical cards: playable only during your own attacks; max 2 tactical cards may affect a single combat.

SCORING (TURN 30)
- If game reaches end of Turn 30 without instant win:
  - 1 VP per controlled hex
  - 2 VP per building
  - Units: Tier1=1 VP, Tier2=3 VP, Tier3=5 VP
  - 3 VP per objective hex controlled
  - +5 VP if your Capital survives

